typeDescriptions.typeString: function (address,enum IPolicyBookFabric.ContractType,string memory,string memory) returns (contract PolicyBook)

attributes.type: function (address,enum IPolicyBookFabric.ContractType,string memory,string memory) returns (contract PolicyBook)

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._contract: is contract address to lookup for created IPolicyBook

returns._policyBook: is policy book address if exists for passed contract address, if not it will return address(0)

params._limit: is number of policy books to returns from _offset
params._offset: is starting item in array to return array from

returns._policyBooksCount: is updated number of policy books

returns._policyBookCount: is number of created policy books

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

policyBookFor(address).notice: Return created Policy Book contract, access: ANY

policyBooks(uint256,uint256).notice: Returns number of created Policy Book contracts address, access: ANY

policyBooksCount().notice: Returns number of created Policy Book contracts, access: ANY
